<item>
            <title>[MATH-1036] GradStructure: A DerivativeStructure that works for large number of variables.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-1036</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Ran into problems with DerivativeStructure today. It requires a lot of&lt;br/&gt;
memory with 6000 or so independent variables. The problem starts with the number of DSCompiler objects instantiated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is a faster/leaner(less memory) GradStructure that only computes up to the first derivative for the case where there are a large number of independent variables.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12669464">MATH-1036</key>
            <summary>GradStructure: A DerivativeStructure that works for large number of variables.</summary>
