                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13771931" author="ajo.fod" created="Thu, 19 Sep 2013 14:21:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changed the name to GradStructure to reflect the relationship with the more generic DerivativeStructure and the idea that it is limited to computing gradients.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13771933" author="ajo.fod" created="Thu, 19 Sep 2013 14:24:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;IMHO: This can be extended to higher orders using more complex hashmap key structure.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13772538" author="ajo.fod" created="Fri, 20 Sep 2013 00:56:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A patch with a few tests are  included here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13806302" author="luc" created="Sun, 27 Oct 2013 10:10:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in subversion as of r1536073.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The name of the class has been changed to SparseGradient and the factory methods for constant and variables changed from get to create.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The RealFieldElement&amp;lt;SparseGradient&amp;gt; interface is implemented, meaning instances can be used in the same kind of computation as all other field elements, including with functions like trigonometric, hyperbolic or power functions. The high accuracy linear combinations are also available for these instances.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report and the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14001815" author="luc" created="Mon, 19 May 2014 15:13:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing all resolved issue now available in released 3.3 version.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
